\begin{exercise}
Use the distributive property to simplify the expression.
\end{exercise}

\begin{solution}
We can use the distributive property to simplify the expression.

First, we can distribute the $(x-1)$ to the terms inside the parentheses.
$$
\begin{aligned}
& =(2x+3)(x-1) \\
& =2x(x-1)+3(x-1) \\
& =2x^2-2x+3 \\
& =2x^2-5x+3
\end{aligned}
$$

Next, we can distribute the $(2x+3)$ to the terms inside the parentheses.
$$
\begin{aligned}
& =(2x+3)(x-1) \\
& =2x(x-1)+3(x-1) \\
& =2x^2-2x+3(x-1) \\
& =2x^2-2x+3x-3
\end{aligned}
$$

Finally, we can combine like terms.
$$
\begin{aligned}
& =2x^2-5x+3x-3 \\
& =2x^2-8x+3
\end{aligned}
$$ So the answer is $2x^2-8x+3$
\end{solution}
